<br>
My monk can Push mobs pretty far, but he also has the sence to not move forward (whereas the pet will move forward when he needs to).  Course on 99% of the raids I have seen, the melee PC's have acted just as dumb as pets and continually repostioned themselves closer to mobs, and ended up pushing them down halls.<br>
<br>
If PC's stand in one place and don't move forward, once the mob has been pushed out of melee range, then mob will move back to the PC's.  If the PC's don't realize this, they &quot;push&quot; the mob, same thing that pets do.  I am sure &quot;truely uber&quot; guilds know this and utilize it, much better than the &quot;normal guilds&quot;.  <br>
<br>
If ya see a melee move forward on a mob /gu melee001 back up, your pushing..........my pet will be blamed for your ignorance..........  <br>
<br>
But ya really need pets on the oposite side of the melees, since the pets will constantly move forward, to be able to hit.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlemagi>Battlemagi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#333333>(3/6/03 4:00:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8974.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.circleofdreams.com/images/merkaba.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &quot;pet Push&quot;</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>One of the three main tanks in my guild refuses to be MT if pets are allowed. I have noticed pet push, a lot, but to be quite honest I think the beasties' pet pushes even more then ours do.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
